BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Y9-RtAD1gorJE9qaJZ_sA
SUMMARY:Winter Improv Student Showcase
DTSTAMP:20260307T235949Z
DTSTART:20260310T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:Come see the improv stars of the future debut the skills they’v
	e learned in Unexpected Productions’ Improv School.\n\nJoin us tonight at 
	Unexpected Productions’ Market Theater for the Winter Student Showcase! \n
	\nWatch as our talented students—ranging from beginner to advanced levels—
	take the stage to craft spontaneous\, engaging\, and often hilarious impro
	v scenes right before your eyes. Our 300\, 400\, and 500-level students wi
	ll showcase their newly honed skills\, giving you an exclusive preview of 
	the next generation of improv stars. \n\nYou’ll experience a variety of pe
	rformance styles inspired by UP’s mainstage shows\, making for an unpredic
	table and highly entertaining night. Stick around after the show to meet t
	he performers—you’ll be able to say\, “I saw them before they were famous!
	” \n\n6:00pm: Chad Sunday 300\, Bestock 400\, Tim 400\, Tony 500\n\n8:00pm
	: Chad Monday 300\, Chazz 400\, Laurel 400\, Liz 500 \n\nDon’t miss this c
	hance to support our rising improv stars and enjoy an evening of laughter 
	and surprises. See you there!\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/det
	ails/winter-improv-student-showcase/18291128/2026-03-09T00\n\nFrom SEAtoda
	y - Learning & Education
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/winter-improv-student-sho
	wcase/18291128/2026-03-09T00
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\, 1428 Post Alley\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-learning
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Learning & Education
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
