BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fjYJ-7BzD9h_vW65K4-fC
SUMMARY:5th Annual Epoch Symposium: Power of Defiance in the Face of Law
DTSTAMP:20260307T235949Z
DTSTART:20260313T150000Z
DESCRIPTION:5th Annual Epoch Symposium: Power of Defiance in the Face of La
	w\n\n \n\nPresented by Seattle University School of Law\, the Black Law St
	udent Association\, and the Law Review\n\n \n\nDate: Friday\, March 13\, 2
	026\n\nTime: 8:00 AM – 1:30 PM PT \\(11:00 AM – 4:30 PM ET\\)\n\nLocation:
	 Virtual \\(via Zoom\\)\n\n \n\nJoin us for the 5th Annual Epoch Symposium
	\, exploring this year’s powerful theme: Power of Defiance in the Face of 
	Law.\n\nOur distinguished scholars will examine how Black and Brown commun
	ities have historically radicalized the law through acts of resistance. Di
	scussions will explore how legal structures continue to sustain systems of
	 power\, and crucially\, how the law itself can be reclaimed as an instrum
	ent of defiance.\n\nThe program features prominent critical race scholars 
	and practitioners from across the nation engaging in timely discussions on
	 the history of law as both a site of oppression and a tool of defiance.\n
	\n \n\nFeatured Speakers & Highlights\n\nInstitutional Welcome: Kristin Di
	Biase\, Associate Dean for Student Affairs\n\nOpening Remarks: Professor R
	ichard Delgado & Professor Jean Stefancic\n\nKeynote Address: Karen Koehle
	r\, nationally recognized civil rights and personal injury litigator and p
	artner at The Stritmatter Firm.\n\nSpecial Feature: A livestream podcast r
	ecording of The Velvet Hammer\, discussing the legal landscape of current 
	events.\n\nClosing Remarks: Elinor Jones Toutant\, on behalf of BLSA.\n\n 
	\n\nSymposium Schedule\n\nNote: Times listed are in Pacific Time \\(PT\\)\
	n\n8:00 AM: Institutional Welcome: Kristin DiBiase\, Associate Dean for St
	udent Affairs\n\n8:05 AM: Opening Remarks by Prof. Richard Delgado & Prof.
	 Jean Stefancic\n\n8:20 AM: Panel 1\n\n9:25 AM: Panel 2\n\n10:30 AM: Break
	\n\n11:00 AM: Keynote Address by Karen Koehler \\(with Q&A\\)\n\n12:00 PM:
	 Podcast Recording of The Velvet Hammer\n\n12:30 PM: Panel 3\n\n1:30 PM: C
	losing Remarks by Elinor Jones Toutant\n\n \n\nThe Zoom link for this even
	t will be sent to RSVP's a few days before the event.  If you register for
	 the event on or after March 11th\, please reach out to Anita Jahangiri \\
	(ajahangiri@seattleu.edu\\) to receive the link.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amci
	ty.com/events/#/details/5th-annual-epoch-symposium-power-of-defiance-in-th
	e-face-of-law/18260241/2026-03-13T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Learning & Educati
	on
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/5th-annual-epoch-symposiu
	m-power-of-defiance-in-the-face-of-law/18260241/2026-03-13T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-learning
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Learning & Education
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT5H30M
END:VEVENT
